# 1. 波乱の予感

Shizuku: *Sigh* I'm finally done with my homework.
Shizuku: Oh, it's gotten very late. I need to get ready for tomorrow and get some rest.
Shizuku: My uniform looks okay and I've already put the textbooks I need for tomorrow in my bag. That just leaves...
Shizuku: Oh, my phone! I'm always forgetting it, so I really should...
Shizuku: That reminds me... I wonder if the producer for iHaz replied back yet...
Shizuku: They'll need to let us know soon if we're going to be appearing, so I'll check right now.
Shizuku: Let's see... Press the power button and...
Shizuku: Hm...? My screen's still black.
Shizuku: Oh dear. Is it broken? I may need to have a repair person look at it tomorrow...
Shizuku: I'll just ask the others about that email tomorrow.
Shizuku: Still... I can't believe we're really getting a chance to appear on TV as MORE MORE JUMP!
Shizuku: I was hoping that we'd receive an opportunity like this someday, but not this soon.
Shizuku: (We weren't even able to join an agency in the beginning and had no idea if we'd actually be able to do anything as idols.)
Shizuku: (However, against all odds, we succeeded in putting on a solo show, which led to us being asked to appear on TV...)
Shizuku: (And this appearance will give us an opportunity to take a step towards becoming idols who are worthy of doing shows at the Dome.)
Shizuku: (Not only that...)
Shizuku: (But our fans are all looking forward to seeing us in an entirely new format. On TV...)
Shizuku: Our segment is only supposed to be about five minutes long, but I'll need to do my best.
Shizuku: I have to prepare well for this...
Shizuku: *Sigh* I'm running late. Helping the teacher carry all those worksheets took much longer than I expected.
Shizuku: I'm sorry for being a little late, everyone...
Haruka: Oh, Shizuku...
Airi: H-Hey...
Shizuku: Is something wrong? You all seem a bit down for some reason...
Minori: Oh... U-Uhh...
Haruka: Have you had a chance to check your inbox, Shizuku...?
Shizuku: My inbox?
Shizuku: Oh, actually, I haven't... My phone wouldn't turn on when I tried to yesterday and I was thinking about having someone look at it later...
Shizuku: But I realized this morning that it just wasn't charged because the cable wasn't plugged in all the way.
Minori: Haha. Oh, Shizuku...
Shizuku: But you mentioned my inbox. Has our TV appearance been cancelled...?
Airi: No, it hasn't. It's just... We just received word that the MCs for our appearance has changed.
Shizuku: The MC...?
Minori: Yeah... Some members of U-Symphonium were originally scheduled to be the MCs when we appeared...
Minori: But their lead isn't feeling well, so they had to ask a different group to replace them.
Shizuku: No, that's terrible. I really hope she's okay...
Shizuku: So, can you tell me which group is going to be replacing them?
Haruka: The thing is...
Airi: It's Cheerful * Days...
Shizuku: What...?
Member A: Shizuku got another solo photo shoot for a magazine cover. This is clearly favoritism.
Member B: Yeah, I guess a pretty face is all they care about. We're clearly better at singing and dancing than she is.
Member C: You said it...
Member C: I'm glad to finally be rid of her.
Shizuku: I see...
Minori: Shizuku...?
Haruka: How do you feel about this...?
Shizuku: Well... I am a little wary of having to talk to them again...
Shizuku: However, after we decided that we're going to appear on TV, I've been preparing myself for this sort of eventuality.
Airi: Shizuku...
Shizuku: So, please don't worry about me.
Shizuku: More importantly, let's do our best to make the most of our very first appearance on TV!
Haruka: Right...
Minori: Yeah! She's right! Let's do our best!
Minori: Oh, also...! They included a few possible meeting dates in their reply. We wanted to ask which works best for you, Shizuku.
Shizuku: Oh, I see. I'm really sorry for not checking sooner.
Haruka: That's okay. We can check to see which date works best together.
Shizuku: Thank you! I should be free to meet whenever...
